Default the bookmarks toolbar visibility to "never" instead of "newtab".

Firefox ships the bookmarks toolbar visible on about:newtab. Gjoa's
navigation lives in the sidebar (tree tabs); the horizontal bookmarks
strip is visual noise users will universally want hidden. Users can
still re-enable it via View > Toolbars > Bookmarks Toolbar (or set the
pref back to "newtab" / "always" themselves).

diff --git a/browser/app/profile/firefox.js b/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
--- a/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
+++ b/browser/app/profile/firefox.js
@@ -2926,7 +2926,7 @@ pref("browser.toolbars.keyboard_navigation", true);
 // "newtab": Show on the New Tab Page
 // "always": Always show
 // "never": Never show
-pref("browser.toolbars.bookmarks.visibility", "newtab");
+pref("browser.toolbars.bookmarks.visibility", "never");

 // Visibility of the "Show Other Bookmarks" menuitem in the
 // bookmarks toolbar contextmenu.
